cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.DL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper discusses a language for formal mathematical knowledge representation and interchange. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper mentions machine access and knowledge management services. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper discusses the implementation of a software API for MMT-based MKM services. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper discusses a plugin interface for injecting syntactic and semantic idiosyncrasies of individual formal languages. 
- cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is also relevant as the paper discusses a system for managing formal mathematical knowledge.
